Scenario: The Misinterpreted Extension Request
A real-world problem often occurs when a student sends a late-night, informal message to a professor via a non-professional platform like a social media DM instead of a formal email. In this scenario, the student used slang and failed to include a clear subject line or registration number. Consequently, the professor ignored the message, thinking it was spam, and the student missed a major project deadline, leading to a grade penalty.What could have been done differently?
The student should have utilized formal email etiquette by using their college email address and a structured format. A clear subject line, a respectful greeting, and a concise explanation of the situation would have ensured the request was professional and seen on time. This highlights that professional tone and the choice of communication channel are critical for academic success.
